For much of the nation, the first two hours of Super Bowl 50 were nothing but pregame. When halftime finally came, it was on.

British rock band Coldplay was booked as the halftime show's top-biller, and they came out on a stage decked in rainbow. At first, the color seemed a nod to the color scheme on Coldplay's A Head Full of Dreams album cover or their recent video for "A Hymn for the Weekend," set in Mumbai, India, during the Holi festival of color.
